And when Moses said to his people, "O my people, remember Allah's favor upon you when He made prophets among you and made you kings, and gave you what He had not given to anyone of the worlds."
O my people, enter the Holy Land which Allah has assigned to you, and do not turn away from it, lest you become losers.
They said, "O Moses, indeed there is a great nation, and we will not enter it until they leave it."
20:22 The two of them were afraid of those who feared Allah, saying: "Enter them in the gate of Egypt; then when you enter it, then surely you will be victorious, if you are believers."
They said, "O Moses, we will not enter it until they enter it; and your Lord will be your Lord, and you will be victorious."
He said, "My Lord, I have no authority over myself and my brother; so make us go astray from the people and the people of the people."
He said: “They have been forbidden for the years of the years, so they may wander out in the land, so do not grieve against the people.
And recite to them the story of Adam, both of the two sons of Adam, when he desired to hasten the sacrifice of the two of them, and said, "I will surely kill you." He said, "I will surely kill you." He said, "Allah accepts the godfearing."
And if I do not stretch your hand to kill you, I will not stretch out your hand against you to kill me, for I fear Allah, the Lord of the worlds.
I desire that you should have my sin and your sin, and you will be among the dwellers of the Fire, and you will be of the wrongdoers."
Then he killed his brother to kill his brother, and he killed him.
Then Allah sent down a raven from the earth, that he might show him how he had seen his brother. He said, "Woe to me! What is it that I am going to be a raven?" He said, "Woe to me!" And he turned away from his brother.
Thus We decreed for the Children of Israel that whoever kills a soul for a soul or a life in the earth, it shall be as though he slew all mankind, as if he slew all mankind. And whoever saves it, it shall be as if he had saved all mankind. Indeed, Our Messengers came to them with clear proofs, and most surely many of them are transgressors.
The punishment of those who wage war against Allah and His messenger and strive to make mischief in the land is only this, that they should be murdered or crucified or their hands and their feet should be cut off on opposite sides or they should be imprisoned; this shall be as a disgrace for them in this world, and in the hereafter they shall have a grievous chastisement.
Except those who repent before you, then know that Allah is Oft-Forgiving, Most Merciful.
O you who have believed, fear Allah and seek the means of nearness to Him, and strive in His way that you may prosper.
Verily, those who disbelieve (in the Oneness of Allah Islamic Monotheism), if they had all that is in the earth, and if it had come to them from the punishment of the Day of Resurrection, it will not be accepted from them, and they will not be accepted it, and they will have a painful punishment.
They will wish to come out of the Fire, but they will not be able to get it; and they will have a lasting punishment.
The male and female women, male women, male or female; for Allah is Mighty, Wise.
But whoever repents after his crime and does good, he will find Allah Oft-Forgiving, Most Merciful.
Do you not know that Allah is the One Who is the kingdom of the heavens and the earth? He punishes whom He will and forgives whom He wills. And Allah is Able to do all things.
O Prophet! Do not let your grieve grieve you. They are disbelievers who say to their mouths: "We believe,” they say, "We believe not in faith, and their hearts have not come to you." They will not come to you, and they will not come to you, but they will not come to you, but they will not come to you, but they will say to the Jews, "If you are good, you will not have been saved from Allah." They will say, "This is what you are commanded."
Those who listen to the truth are lying in the way of falsehood, but if they come to you, judge between them, or turn away from them. But if they turn away from them, judge between them, and judge between them judge between them. Lo! Allah loves those who do good.
And how can they give you permission until they come to you? The Torah is in Allah's way, then they turn away from it. But they are not believers.
We have sent down the Torah in the Torah, and in the light, and the light, and the prophets, and the Jews, and the Jews, and the Jews, that they were given the Book of God; so fear them not; but fear Me, and fear Me; so fear Me not, and fear Me not.
And We ordained for them in the past, a nose for a man, an eye, a nose, an ear for a tooth, and a tooth for a tooth, and a tooth for a tooth, and a tooth for a tooth, and a tooth for a tooth, and a tooth for a tooth. Whoever does not judge by what Allah has sent down, they are the wrongdoers.
And We sent in their footsteps Jesus son of Mary, confirming that which was before him of the Torah, and We gave him the Gospel, wherein was guidance and light, confirming that which was before it, and that which was before it, and a guidance for those who fear Allah.
And let the People of the Book judge that which Allah has sent down to judge, and those who do not judge in what Allah has sent down, they are the transgressors.
And We have sent down to you the Book with the truth, confirming the Book that is before them, and that which has been sent down to them, so that you may judge between them with what has been revealed to you. And follow not their desires from what has come to you from the truth, and follow not their desires from the truth. And let them not follow your desires, and let them follow you. And if Allah wills, He will have made you one of all that you have given you. Then you will be returned to Allah.
And judge between them with what Allah has revealed to them, and follow not their desires; and fear them with fear from which Allah has sent down to you. But if they turn away, know that Allah will punish them for their sins. But most of mankind are transgressors.
Is it better than the people who wish to be better than God?
O you who believe! Do not take the Jews and the Christians for friends; they are friends of each other; and whoever amongst you takes them for a friend, surely surely he is one of them; surely Allah does not guide the unjust people.
And you will see those in whose hearts is a disease, and they say, "We fear lest a misfortune should befall us." Then Allah will send them a fear from Allah, or send a command from Him, so that their hearts may be forgiven.
And those who believe will say, "Are these the ones who swore by Allah that they would not be with you?"
O you who believe! whoever among you turns away from his religion, then Allah will love him, and will love him with a love of the believers, and they will not strive in the cause of Allah against those who strive against the unbelievers, strive to fight in the cause of Allah. That is the bounty of Allah, whom He wills; and Allah is Ample-giving, Knowing.
“Your friends are only Allah and His Messenger, and the believers, and those who establish the prayer and pay alms, while they are (all) submissive.”
And whoever takes Allah and His Messenger and the believing believers, then surely he is the party of Allah.
O you who believe! Do not take those who have been given the Book before you and those who were before you, and do not take the disbelievers as a mockery for those who have believed. So fear Allah, if you are believers.
And when you call to prayer, they take it as mockery and sport; this is because they are a people who do not understand.
Say: "O people of the Scripture! do you find no fault for us except that we believe in Allah and what has been sent down to us and that which has been revealed to us, and that most of you are transgressors?"
Say: "Shall I inform you of a worse punishment from Allah? Those who incurred wrath from Allah and those who were cursed by apes and swine and swine, those who worshipped Satan, they are worse and worse, and they are far astray from the path of evil."
And when they come to you, they say, "We believe in it, but they are in the midst of those who disbelieve; and Allah knows best what they conceal."
And you see many of them see the sin of sin, and the devouring of what is forbidden, and that which they have done is evil.
And why do they not forbid the rabbis and the things of their own hands, and from what they have forbidden? Evil is what they used to do.
And the Jews said: "Allah's plan is with the poor." They said, "They are not with those who have been proud of their hands." But they are not in the hands of their own hands, but it is only that they are in the hands of your Lord, and that it may be for them from your Lord. That is what has been revealed to you from your Lord, and in the end of the Day of Resurrection, they will have a share of what has been revealed to them. And Allah will not make mischief in the land, and Allah does not love the arrogant.
And if the People of the Book had believed and feared Allah, We would have removed their sins and admitted them to gardens of bliss.
And if they had been sent down to the Torah and the Gospel, and what has been sent down to them from their Lord, they would have taken out of them out of their hands and from their feet; but most of them are most disobedient.
O Messenger! deliver what has been revealed to you from your Lord. Do not follow it. But if you do not do it not, Allah will protect you from the people; and Allah will protect you from the people; surely Allah does not guide the unbelieving people.
Say: "O people of the Scripture, you have no right to stand on you until you follow the Torah and the Gospel and that which has been revealed to you from your Lord."
Those who believe, and those who are Jews, and the Sabians, and the Sabians, whoever believes in Allah and the Last Day and does good, there shall be no fear for them, nor shall they grieve.
We took the Children of Israel with the Children of Israel, and We sent messengers to them with their own souls, so that no one of them did not desire their hearts, and they rejected some of them, and they slew others.
And they thought that it was not a trial, so they became blind and deaf, so Allah turned back towards them. But most of them became blind and deaf; and Allah sees what they do.
Surely they say, "The Messiah, son of Mary, is Allah's son." And the Messiah said, "O Children of Israel, worship Allah, my Lord and your Lord. That is what Allah has forbidden for those who associate partners with Allah, and his abode will be the Fire; and the wrongdoers will be helpers.
Those who say: "These are the helpers of Allah." There is no god but Allah. There is no god save Him. But if they do not desist, then woe to those who disbelieve.
Why do they not turn back to Allah and ask His forgiveness? And Allah is Oft-forgiving, Most Merciful.
The Messiah, son of Mary, was no more than a Messenger. Messengers passed away from him, and his mother said to his mother, "Indeed, we eat food with food. Look at them, see how We make clear to them. See how they are deluded."
Say (O Muhammad SAW): "Do you worship besides Allah that which is no harm or benefit for you? Allah is All-hearing, All-knowing."
Say: "O people of the Scripture, do not exceed your religion in the religion of the truth, do not follow the desires of the people, and do not follow the desires of the people who have gone astray before them."
Those who disbelieved among the Children of Israel were cursed by the tongue of David and Jesus son of Mary. That was because they disobeyed and persisted.
They did not forbid one another from what they used to do, and what they used to do.
You see many of them befriending those who disbelieve. Evil is that which their souls have sent forward before them. They will have a curse against Allah, and they will have a lasting punishment.
And if they had believed in Allah and His Messenger and what was revealed to him, they would not have taken them as friends, but most of them are transgressors.
