O you who believe! intoxicants and gambling, and divining arrows and divining arrows are only Satan's handiwork; so fear them so that you may prosper.
Satan wants to eat you with intoxicants and hatred, and that you may not be able to make enmity between you and from the remembrance of Allah. Will you not then desist?
And obey Allah and obey the Messenger; and fear Him, if you turn back, then know that the Messenger is only to convey the message.
There is no blame for those who believe and do good deeds for what they have earned, and believe and believe, and do righteous deeds, and fear Allah and believe and do good, and Allah loves those who do good.
O you who believe! Allah has promised you to be a slave of that which is in your hands, or that it may be that you may know that Allah knows what is in the hearts, and that He may test those who fear Him.
O you who believe! Do not exult in the land, and you will not be able to kill you; and whoever dies, then you shall have a double of the two of you. Let him not be a slave for you, or let the poor eat for you, or let the poor eat for you, or let the poor, or let the poor eat, or let it be for the poor; for Allah is Strong, Mighty.
It is for the sea for you to eat for the sea, and it is for you to eat for it and for you for the pilgrimage, and in the land you have been forbidden. And fear Allah, and fear Allah, to Him you will be gathered.
Allah has made the Ka'bah in the Ka'bah, the Sacred House, and the people, and the people, and the people, and the people, so that you may know that Allah knows what is in the heavens and whatever is in the earth, and Allah knows all things.
Know that Allah is severe in punishment, and that Allah is Oft-Forgiving, Most Merciful.
The duty of the Messenger is only to convey the message, and Allah knows what you conceal and what you conceal.
Say: "The hypocrites are not the good and the needy, even though the evil ones may benefit you. So fear Allah, so that you may be successful."
O you who believe! Do not ask about any of them who are truthful to you, if you should be able to ask you about the Qur'an, then if you ask about the Qur'an, it is clear to you, and Allah will forgive you. Allah is Forgiving, Forbearing.
A people before you asked about you, and they disbelieved in it.
Allah has not ordained for you a dream, or a <unk>, or a <unk>, or a polytheist, and the disbelievers, they deny Allah; but most of them do not understand.
