O you who believe! Be sure for your own souls. If you are guided, you will not find any harm from your own soul. To Allah you will be returned to all that you did, and He will inform you of what you used to do.
O you who believe! When death approaches you, they are two believers, so that they may be better than you. But if you are in the land, then you are only in the land; then if you are in the land, then then you shall be brought back to the earth, then if you doubt them, then then you shall be called back to the two months, and if you have no doubt, then then they will have a share of Allah.
But if it should be that they should be guilty of the sin of the two men, they shall have two of their wives, except by their wives, and they will swear by Allah: "Our testimony is truer than the testimony of our testimony." And they said: "Our testimony is truer than the truth, and we have not transgressed."
It is nearer to them that they may bear witness to the truth, or that they may be afraid of their oaths; and fear Allah, and fear Allah; and Allah does not guide the unjust people.
On the Day when Allah will gather all His Messengers, He will say: "What is your response?" They said: "We have no knowledge of this."
And when Jesus, son of Mary, said, "My Lord, I have vowed to you the favor of my mother, and that I may love you with those whom I have bestowed on you, and the people who are in the Book will have no power in the sight of the people, and they will have the Book and the Gospel, and they will have the Book of God, and they will not be able to follow it, and when they were given it, it will be said to them, "This is nothing but obvious magic." And when they came to you, they said, "This is nothing but obvious magic."
And when I inspired the disciples, "Believe in Me and My Messenger,” they said, "We believe, bear witness that we are Muslims."
And when the disciples said, "O Jesus, son of Mary, will your Lord send down to us a table from heaven?"
They said: "We wish to eat from it and our hearts, and we know that the truth has come to us, and that you may bear witness of the truth."
Jesus, son of Mary, said: "O Allah, our Lord, send down to us a table table from heaven, so that it may be for us the first of us and the last of us. You are a sign for us and a sign from Thee. You are the best of providers."
Allah said: "I am sent down to you (O Muhammad sal-Allaahu 'alayhe wa sallam), then I send down to you (Muhammad SAW) after that, and if I disobey you, I will punish him with a severe torment."
And when Allah will say, "O Jesus, son of Mary, did you say to the people, ‘Take me and my mother besides Allah?' He will say, ‘Glory be to you, my Lord, I am not truthful.’
I said not to them aught except what Thou didst command me: "Worship Allah, my Lord and your Lord." But when I dwelt among them, Thou wast a watcher over them; while Thou didst take me up, Thou wast the Watcher over them, and Thou art the Knower of all things.
If You punish them, they are Your servants, and if You forgive them, You are the All-Mighty, the All-Wise.
Allah will say: "This is a Day of truth that will benefit their truthfulness with truth; theirs will be gardens beneath which rivers flow; they will abide therein forever. Allah is pleased with them. That is the great triumph.
To Allah belongs the dominion of the heavens and the earth and all that is in them, and He has power over all things.
All praise belongs to Allah, Who created the heavens and the earth, and made the light, and the light, so that the disbelievers are equal to the Lord.
He it is Who created you from clay, then decreed a term for him, and a term appointed for him; then you will not doubt.
And Allah is the One Who is in the heavens and the earth, and He knows what you have hidden and what you do.
There is no sign of the signs of their Lord, but they turn away from it.
But they denied the truth when it came to them, but they will come to them with a painful punishment.
Have they not seen how many generations We have destroyed before them, and We have established on the earth a great authority in which We have not established you, and We caused the sky to flow beneath them, and rivers flow beneath them, and We caused them to grow in the midst of their sins, and We destroyed them among them.
And if We had sent down to you a Book from paper, they would have touched their hands, and they would have said, "This is nothing but obvious magic."
And they say, "Why has not been sent down to him from the angels?" And if We had sent down an angel, it would have been decreed for them, but they would not be reprieved.
And if We had made him an angel, We would have made him a human being, and We would have made them in the matter that they would have been confused.
And indeed Messengers were mocked before you, but they mocked at them that they mocked with them.
Say: "Travel in the land and see how was the end of the rejecters."
Say: "To whom belongs the dominion of the heavens and the earth?" Say: "He is the One Who gives mercy on whom He will. He will gather you on the Day of Resurrection concerning the Day of Resurrection. He will not gather you with the Day of Resurrection."
To Him belongs all that is in the night and the day, and He is the All-hearing, the All-knowing.
Say: "Who is the Lord of the heavens and the earth, besides whom He will not give provision?" Say: "I am commanded to be the first of those who submit to Him." Say: "I am commanded to be the first of those who believe."
Say (O Muhammad SAW): "I fear not if my Lord should punish me on the Day of Resurrection."
On the Day when it will be averted from him, Allah will have mercy on him; and this is a great triumph.
And if Allah touches you with affliction, none can remove it except Him; and if He touches you with good, He has power over all things.
He is the Omnipotent, the Wise.
Say: "What is the matter with you?" Say: "I bear witness that Allah is witness of you and that which is revealed to you." And the Qur'an has been revealed to me, and that you may warn those who are warned from the truth. Do you not think that Allah will give you a witness?
Those whom We have given the Book know that they recognize their sons; they will not believe in their own souls.
Who is more unjust than one who invents a lie against Allah or rejects His signs? Indeed, the wrongdoers will not be successful.
And on the Day when We shall gather them all together, then We will say to those who associated partners with Allah, "Where are your associates?"
But they will not be able to say to them, “By Allah, our Lord, we have no partners.”
See how they used to lie against them, and then they turned away from them.
And among them are some who listen to thee, and We have hearts whose hearts have ears to understand them, and deafness not in their ears; but if they see every sign, they will not believe in them; they will not believe until they come with thee. The unbelievers say: "These are nothing but tales of the ancients."
And they prohibit (others) from it, and they turn away from them, and they do not destroy themselves except themselves, and they do not know.
And if you could see when they will be in the Fire, they will say, "Oh, would that we would be brought back, and we would not deny the signs of our Lord, and we would not have been believers."
Nay, it was to come to them before that which they used to hide, and if they were to return to it, they would have been cast away from what they have been forbidden; surely they are indeed liars.
And they say: "There is nothing but the life of this world, and we shall not be resurrected."
And if you could see, when they are before their Lord, He will say, "Is this not the truth?" They will say, "Yes, by our Lord!" He will say, "Taste the punishment of your Lord."
They are those who deny the meeting of Allah. When the Hour comes to them, they will say: "Woe to us!" They will say, "Woe to us! Alas for us for what they used to do." They will bear their burdens on their burdens.
And the life of this world is nothing but amusement and amusement; and the home of the Hereafter is better for those who fear Allah. Will you not then understand?
Verily, We know that they will not grieve you with what they say, but they say, "You are not a liar."
And indeed Messengers were denied before you, but they were patient and patient until Our help came to them. And none can alter the words of Allah; and there is none who can alter the words of Allah.
And if their aversion should be hard for you, then if you find a tunnel on the earth or a ladder of heaven, or bring a sign to them, let them bring them a sign; and if Allah willed, He will have guided them all, so do not be of the ignorant.
Those who listen to the call will be called to Allah on the Day of Resurrection; and Allah will gather them on the Day of Resurrection.
And they say: "Why has not a sign sent down to him from his Lord?" Say: "Allah has sent down a sign, but most of them know not."
And there is no creature in the earth, nor a bird, nor can they look at its wings, but they are like the people of the Book. We do not follow anything but the Book of their Lord.
And those who deny Our Ayat (proofs, evidences, verses, lessons, signs, revelations, etc.) are deaf and dumb, but Allah leaves whom He will astray, and He guides whom He wills to the straight path.
Say: "Have you considered, if the punishment of Allah comes upon you or the Hour, if you are truthful?"
Nay, but they call upon Him, so that you may call upon Him, and that you will be called to Him, and you will not forget what you associate with Him.
And indeed We sent Messengers before you, and We seized them with distress and hardship so that they might humble themselves.
So when Our punishment came to them suddenly, they did not think that their hearts were hardened, and their hearts were hardened, and Satan made them attractive to them.
So when they forgot what they were reminded of, We opened them all of the gates of all that they had given them, and We seized them with what they used to do.
And the people of the evildoers were cut off, and all praise belongs to Allah, the Lord of the worlds.
Say: "Have you considered, if Allah should take away your hearing and your sight, and set up your hearts, that He will bring you back from the other, but that He may bring you back?"
Say: "Tell me, if the punishment of Allah comes upon you suddenly or openly, will they not destroy the people of the wrong-doers?"
And We have sent the Messenger and the givers of glad tidings to those who have faith, and those who believe, there shall be no fear on them, nor shall they grieve.
And for those who reject Our Ayat (proofs, evidences, verses, lessons, signs, revelations, etc.), they will have a painful punishment for them.
Say: "I do not say to you that I possess the treasures of Allah, nor do I know that I am the Knower of the Unseen, and I do not follow anything but that which has been revealed to me." Say: "Are the blind and the blind?" Say, "Are the blind and the like of the blind?"
And fear those who fear their Lord with fear of their Lord, and they will not have any protector besides Allah, and that they may be godfearing.
And do not turn away from those who call upon their Lord in the morning and evening, seeking His pleasure, for they have no portion of what they have earned, nor do you have any share for them. You will turn away from them, and you will be among the wrongdoers.
And thus We made some of them so that they might say: "Are these the people whom Allah has bestowed with us?" Allah does not know the grateful people.
And when those who believe in Our Ayat (proofs, evidences, verses, lessons, signs, revelations, etc.) come to you, say: "Peace be upon you," so that your Lord has mercy upon you, so that you may do evil in ignorance, and then repent and act righteously, then He is Forgiving, Merciful.
And thus do We explain the Ayat (proofs, evidences, verses, lessons, signs, revelations, etc.), so that they may be guided.
Say: "I am forbidden to worship those whom you call upon besides Allah. Say: I am not responsible for your desires; I am not going to follow your desires, and I am not of the guided."
Say: "I am indeed a clear proof from your Lord, and you deny it, for I am not responsible for what you desire to hasten." It is only Allah who gives the truth to the truth, and He is the best of deciders.
Say: "If you were to hasten for me, I would have been brought to you in the matter, and Allah knows best the wrongdoers."
To Him belongs the keys of the unseen. He knows what is in the earth, and He knows what is in the sea, and it is not a leaf, nor a leaf, nor a leaf, nor a leaf, nor the earth, nor the earth, nor any tree.
He it is Who takes your souls by night, and He knows what you have done by day; then He raises you up again that a specified term may be fulfilled; then to Him is your return; then He will inform you of what you did.
He is the One Who takes His servants over His servants, and He sends you up from the dead, when death approaches them, and they will not die, and they will not be able to do anything.
Then they will be returned to their Lord, to Him belongs the truth; and He is the swiftest of the reckoning.
Say: "Who delivers you from the darkness of the land and the sea, when you call upon Him in humility and in secret?" Say: "If we give us thanks from Allah, we shall surely be of the thankful."
Say (O Muhammad SAW): "Allah will protect you from your distress and from every distress, then you will be set up (with Him)."
Say: "He will have power upon you from above you, or from your feet, or from your feet, or some of you will make some of you make some of you, and We will make some of you taste some of them, so see how We explain the communications."
And your people deny it, and it is the truth. Say: "I am not responsible for you."
Every time will come to you, and you will know.
And when you see those who dispute in Our Ayat (proofs, evidences, verses, lessons, signs, revelations, etc.), turn away from them, turn away from them. But if Satan touches you, then do not follow the people of the unjust.
“And those who fear Allah will not be accountable for them, but they may be reminded of them so that they may fear Allah.”
And (as for) those who take a religion for their religion and play themselves, and let them present the life of this world, and warn them with the Qur'an, so that they may not be able to leave their own souls. They will have no protector besides Allah. They will have no protector besides Allah, and they will have no protector. They will have no protector. They will have no protector. They will have a painful punishment.
Say: "Shall we call upon Allah that which does not benefit us nor harm him, and then turn away from him from whom Allah has guided us?
And establish prayer, and fear Him, and be careful of Him to Whom you will be gathered.
And it is He Who created the heavens and the earth with truth, and He will say to the Day of Resurrection: "Be!" and it will be that the Day of Judgment will be fulfilled; and the trumpet will be blown on the Day of Resurrection. He is the All-Wise, the All-wise.
And when Ibrahim said to his father, Azar, "Do you take idols as gods?" And I will see you, "You are indeed a plain people."
And thus did We show Abraham the kingdom of the heavens and the earth, that he might be of those who have certitude.
When the night saw him, he saw a star, he said, "This is my Lord." But when they set up, he said, "I do not love anything."
When he saw the moon rising, he said, "This is my Lord!" But when he said, "If my Lord does not guide me, I will surely be among the people who have gone astray."
When he saw the sun rising in splendor, he said: "This is my Lord!" But when he said, "My people, I am like the people who associate with you, and I am innocent of what you associate with me."
Indeed, I have turned away from Him who is the One who created the heavens and the earth, and I am not of the polytheists.
And his people argued with him. He said, "Do you argue with me about Allah? I have guided me to the right path, so I fear that I should not fear what you associate with me. My Lord encompasses all things in knowledge."
And fear I fear that I should fear what you associate with Allah, while you fear not that Allah has sent down to you no authority from which He has not sent down to you any authority? But if you know that the two parties is better than one another.
Those who believe and do not believe in their belief, for them is a safe path, and they are guided.
And indeed, our argument is to be fulfilled for Abraham from his people. We will raise him in degrees whom We will. Your Lord is All-Wise, All-Knowing.
And We gave Abraham Isaac and Jacob, and We guided him with the guidance of Noah and his descendants, and Solomon, and Joseph, and Aaron, and Moses, and Aaron, and Moses, and Aaron, and thus We reward the virtuous.
And Zechariah and John, and Elias, and Elias, and each of them were righteous.
And Ismail, and Elisha, and Lot, and Lot, and all of them We preferred above the nations.
And among their fathers, and their brothers, and their brothers, and We guided them and guided them to the right path.
Allah guides whom He will of His servants, and He guides whom He will.
These are the ones whom We gave to the Book and wisdom and prophethood; so if they do not believe in it, We have already made a people who disbelieve not in it.
These are the ones whom Allah has guided, so follow them. Say: "I ask of you no reward for this. This is a Reminder for all mankind."
And they did not believe with Allah, because they said, "Why has not been sent down to us from Allah?" Say: "He has sent down the Book from the Book to the people who did not believe." Say: "The Book has been sent down to you from the people, and that you may make it clear to you." Say, "Allah has given you the Book, and that you may hide them." Say, "Allah has revealed the Book." Say, "Allah has revealed the Book."
And this is a Book which We have blessed before you, confirming that which is before it, and that you may warn the Mother of Cities and the people who believe in the Hereafter believe in it. And those who believe in the Hereafter believe in it, and they are their prayers.
And who is more unjust than he who invents a lie against Allah or says, "What has been revealed to me?" And he said, "I have been sent down to the Book." Say, "I have sent down the Book which Allah has sent down to you. If you see it, then the angels will be judged by the angels." And if you see it, then the angels will be rewarded with their own souls, and you will not be able to kill them.
And indeed, you shall come to Us, except that We created you first, and We have left you behind your backs, and We have not seen you with those who have not seen you. We do not see you with those whom you used to associate with Allah. Indeed, you are among the witnesses, and you are the witnesses of your idols.
It is Allah Who splits the grain of grain and the grain of grain, the living and the dead, the living of the living. That is Allah, the One, how are you turned away; how are you deluded?
It is the dawn, the day, the rest, and the night, and the sun, and the moon; for He is the Mighty, the Wise.
And He it is Who has made the stars subservient to you, that you may help the children of the sea and the sea in the depths of the sea. Verily, We have made clear to people the signs of the people.
And He it is Who has created you from a single soul, then it is a resting place and its resting-place. We have made clear to you a sign for a people who have understanding.
And He it is Who sends down water from the sky, then We bring forth fruits from every kind of grain, which We have brought forth from it; and from the date of the trees there are clusters, and pomegranates, and pomegranates, and pomegranates, and pomegranates, and pomegranates, and pomegranates, and pomegranates, and pomegranates, and pomegranates, and pomegranates, when they are a people who believe.
And those who associate partners with Allah set up partners in the sight of those who have taken themselves, and they are sons of what they have taught; Glory be to Him, above what they attribute, and He is exalted above what they do.
Who is the Creator of the heavens and the earth? He is a son, and He has created all things. He has created all things, and He has knowledge of all things.
That is Allah, your Lord, there is no god but He, the Creator of all things; so worship Him. He is the Guardian of all things.
He comprehends not the vision, but He comprehends the eyes; and He is the Subtle, the Wise.
Indeed, there has come to you from your Lord with clear proofs; so whoever sees it will be for his own soul, and whosoever blinds himself will be his own loss, and I am not a keeper over you.
And thus do We explain the Ayat (proofs, evidences, verses, lessons, signs, revelations, etc.), that they may say: "You have studied (the Qur'an), and that We may make it a sign for people who know."
Follow what has been revealed to you from your Lord; there is no god save Him, and turn away from the polytheists.
And if Allah had pleased, they would not have taken partners with Him; and We have not made you a keeper over them, and you are not of them.
Do not revile those whom they call upon besides Allah, lest they revile Allah with knowledge, and that every word may be made fair for them; so that they may have their own deeds; then their Lord will return to them, and He will inform them of what they used to do.
And they swear by Allah by their strongest oaths that if a sign had come to them, they would believe in it. Say: "These are the signs of Allah." Say: "These are the signs of Allah that you may not believe."
And We shall turn their hearts and their eyes, and their eyes will not be accepted before them, and We will leave them in their rebellion in their rebellion.
And if We had sent down to them angels, and the dead speak to them, and We would have gathered all things with their eyes, they would not believe in it, but most of them would not believe.
And thus have We made for every prophet an enemy from among men and jinn, and some of the devils deceive each other. But if your Lord had willed, they would not have done it, so they would not have done it, and they will mislead them.
And so that the hearts of those who do not believe in the Hereafter may incline to it, and that they may be pleased with it, and that they may have their deeds.
Say: "Shall I seek other than Allah other than Allah, when He has sent down to you the Book (the Qur'an) which has been sent down to you from the Book? Those who have been given the Book know that it has been revealed to you from your Lord.
And the word of your Lord is true in truth and in justice; none can change His words; and He is the All-hearing, the All-knowing.
And if you obey most of those on earth, they will mislead you from the path of Allah. They follow only conjecture and follow it.
Your Lord knows best who has strayed from His path, and He knows best those who are guided.
If you believe in Allah, then you will be in your faith.
And what is the matter for you that you do not eat from the name of Allah that which has been mentioned to you in the name of Allah? It is not lawful for you that you may have knowledge. But most of them follow their own desires. Surely, your Lord knows best the transgressors.
And turn away from the sin and the sin; for those who commit sins will be recompensed for what they used to earn.
And eat not that which is not mentioned in the name of Allah, for that is wrong, and that the evil of the devils may make their friends manifest; and if they obey them, they will argue with them, and if ye obey them, ye shall surely be sharers.
Is it not that We gave him life, and We made him a light of a light, whose people are like the like of the people who are in the hearts of the people? But it is not for those who disbelieved, because of what they did.
And in every city, We have made in every city a guilty criminals, so that they may conspire in it, and they do not deceive themselves except themselves, and they do not know.
And when a sign comes to them, they say: "We will not believe in it until they have been given the Messengers of Allah." Allah knows best what He has sent down to His Messenger. Those who commit evil will have a painful punishment from Allah. They will have a painful punishment.
And whomsoever Allah wills to guide, He expands his breast to Islam, and whomsoever He wills, He makes his breast narrow and constricted, as if he were climbing down into heaven, then Allah will punish those who believe.
And this is a straight path from your Lord. We have indeed explained Our signs for a people who believe.
They will have their abode with their Lord, and He will reward them with what they used to do.
And on the Day when He will gather them all together, and He will say: "O mankind! Lo! the people of the jinn are among you." They will say: "Our Lord! We have made some of us excel others with others." They will say: "Your Lord! Lo! your abode is for us, and that ye may abide in the Fire." He will say: "Enter your home."
And thus do We make the wrong-doers among those who do wrong for what they used to earn.
O mankind, have not messengers come to you from among the people of men and men, who have come to you with My signs and warning you from the meeting of this Day of yours? They will say, "We bear witness against them, and bear witness to them." They will say, "We bear witness against them."
That is because your Lord will not destroy the towns unjustly, but they are unaware of their people.
Each of them are degrees of what they do, and your Lord is not unaware of what they do.
And your Lord is Rich, Most Merciful, and if He wills, He will destroy you from your sins, and appoint for you whom He will of the nations among you.
Verily, it is that which you have promised, and you will not escape.
Say: "O my people! I am acting to your own souls, and I am acting to you, and you will surely know that the righteous will be in the Hereafter; surely the wrongdoers will not prosper."
And they assign to Allah a portion of the tilth and cattle that He has created for them, and they say: "This is for Allah." They said: "This is for Allah." So they will not reach their partners with Allah. And whatever they associate with their associates, they will not reach their own souls. What is what they used to do.
And as for those who associate their partners in the religion of Allah, they would have made their children attractive to them, and their religion increased them in their religion. Had Allah willed, they would not have done it, and they will have nothing to fabricate.
And they say, "These are the cattle, and the tilth, and the tilth, except that they may not eat anything except for them." They say, "It is forbidden for the cattle, and cattle, and cattle, and cattle, for Allah's name, they will not be able to give them a lie."
And they say: "Whatever is in the bellies of the cattle is that which is in the bellies of the cattle, and for our wives." But if they die, they will have their own souls; and if they are dead, they will have their reward; surely Allah is All-Knowing, All-knowing.
Those who have lost their children without knowledge without knowledge, and what Allah has provided for them, they fabricate against Allah a lie against Allah. Surely, they have gone astray, and they are not guided.
And it is He who has produced the gardens and the gardens, and the trees, and the trees, and the trees, and the trees, and the trees, and the trees, and the trees, and the trees, and the fruit thereof, and its fruits, and the harvest thereof, and the harvest thereof; and not do not commit excess.
And the cattle and the cattle are made for you, and eat of what Allah has provided for you, and do not follow the footsteps of Satan; surely he is to you a clear enemy.
(27) (87) And from the tribe of sheep, and of the goats, and of women, and of women, or the two females, or the two females, or the two females, or the two females, or the two females?
And of the pair of the camels and of the two of them, or the two females, or the two females, or the two females, or the two females, or the two females, or when Allah has enjoined you? What is the matter of Allah? He is more unjust than those who lie against him. And most surely Allah does not guide the unjust people.
Say: "I do not spend in what has been revealed to me that I should eat for the forbidden of what has been revealed to them, or blood, or blood, or blood, or eat of it, for that which is in the name of the name of Allah, is no more than the name of the name of Allah, and in sin; for your Lord is Oft-forgiving, Most Merciful."
And We have forbidden the Jews, all of the trees, and the sheep, and the sheep, and the cattle, or the cattle, or their mothers, or their mothers, or their mothers, or their mothers, and We punished them with their deeds; and indeed we shall be truthful.
But if they deny you, say: "Your Lord is the Lord of all the people, and His punishment will not be averted from His people."
They will say: "Had Allah willed, we would not have worshipped us, nor our fathers, nor would we have forbidden us." But those before them said, "We have denied those before them." Say: "This is nothing but your proof." Say: "Bring us your proof." Say: "This is nothing but a clear proof."
Say: "Allah is the One, if He willed, He would have guided you all.
Say (O Muhammad SAW): "Say to those who bear witness to their fathers, if they bear witness to them, do not bear witness with them, and those who reject Our Ayat (proofs, evidences, verses, lessons, signs, revelations, etc.) do not speak to them, and those who reject Our Ayat (proofs, evidences, verses, lessons, signs, revelations, etc.) do not speak to them.
Say: "I have forbidden you to follow your Lord, so that you may not associate anything with Him, and do not kill your parents, and do not kill your children. Do not kill your children, and do not kill your children. Do not kill your children, and do not kill them. That is what God has given you. That is what you do."
And do not approach the property of the property of the orphan, except that when its soul is fulfilled, and give full measure and weight in full measure. We do not burden any human soul beyond its capacity. And when you speak justice, it is better for you. And when you speak justice, it is just that you may be admonished.
And this is My Straight Path, so follow it, and do not follow the paths of others; they will not leave you from His way. Thus He commands you that you may be godfearing.
Then We gave Moses the Book, completing the favour of Allah, and explaining everything, and a guidance and a mercy, that they may believe in their Lord.
And this is a blessed Book which We have sent down, so follow it, and fear that you may receive mercy.
Lest you not say: "The Book has been sent down before us from the two sects, and we were unaware of it."
Or lest they should say, "If the Book had been sent down to us, they would have been better guided than them." Then there is a clear proof from your Lord, and a guidance from your Lord. And who is more unjust than he who rejects the communications of Allah and turns away from them? We will punish those who turn away from Our signs. We shall have a painful punishment.
Do they not wait for that which is sent down to them from the angels or from your Lord, or from your Lord's signs? On the Day of Resurrection, there will be no more than a sign for the people of your Lord. On the Day of Resurrection, the people will not believe in it. Say: "Wait for us." Say: "Wait!"
“Those who have divided their religion and sects, you have no authority in them; but their affair is with Allah; then He will inform them of what they used to do.”
Whoever brings a good deed will be tenfold like a little like it, and whoever does evil will be recompensed for it, and they will not be wronged.
Say: “My Lord has guided me to a straight path, a right religion, the religion of Abraham.
Say: "Verily, my prayer, my sacrifice, my life, and my dying are for Allah, the Lord of the worlds."
I am not associate with Him, and I am the first of those who believe and I am the first of those who submit.
Say: "Shall I seek other than Allah as a Lord? He is the Lord of all things, and every soul shall not bear any burden except by any soul; and then shall there be no burden with any soul with another. Then shall ye be brought back to your Lord."
And He it is Who has made you inheritors of the earth, and He has made some of you excel others above others, that He may test you in that which He has given you; surely your Lord is swift in retribution; surely He is the Forgiving, the Merciful.
Alif Lam Mim.
The Book has sent down to you (O Muhammad SAW) that you may warn them (O Muhammad SAW), so that you may warn (them) with it in your heart, and that you may be admonished.
Follow what has been sent down to you from your Lord, and do not follow the guardians of those who do not follow the other. Little are little.
And how many a township have We destroyed; then Our punishment came to them, or they were sleeping at night.
And when Our punishment came to them, they said: "We are not the wrongdoers."
Then We will question those who have been sent to Our Messengers, and We will question the messengers.
Then We will inform them of what We have taught them, and we are not of it.
And on the Day of Resurrection, the truth will be true, and those whose scales are heavy will be successful.
And as for those whose scales are light, they will have their own souls, because they deny Our revelations.
And indeed We have established you in the earth, and provided therein therein for you. Little little are you grateful.
And indeed We created you, then We gave you the angels, then We said to the angels, "Prostrate to Adam." They prostrated themselves except Iblis. They prostrated not except Iblis.
He said, "What prevented you?" He said, "I am better than you." He said, "I am better than me. You created me from fire, and You created him from clay."
He said, "Go down from the sky, and do not exult in it. You are the ones who are the losers.
He said, "Allow me respite till the Day of Resurrection."
He said: "You are the most respited of them."
He said, "You have led me astray because of your own souls; I will find you in a way of humiliation."
Then I will come to them from before them and from behind them, from their right, and from their left, and You will not find most of them thankful."
He said, "Depart from the sky, and go away from them, and I will fill you with the fire of Hell."
"O Adam! dwell with your wife and your wife, and eat therefrom therefrom, but do not approach this tree, lest ye be of the wrongdoers."
Then Satan whispered to them in order to whisper to them that which was hidden from them of their shame, and said, "Your Lord has forbidden you from this tree lest you should become angels or become angels."
And he swore to them: "I am indeed a believer.
Then they plotted against them, so they tasted the tree, and when they tasted it, their shame came out of them, and they began to say to themselves, "Did I not forbid you of the tree of the Garden?" And their Lord called them out of the Garden, and said to them, "I did not forbid you of any tree."
They said, "Our Lord, we have wronged ourselves, and if You do not forgive us, do not have mercy on us, we will surely be of the losers."
He said, "Go, you are one of the two enemies of one another, and you are an enemy for the earth and a provision for a time."
He said: Therein shall ye live, and therein shall ye die, and from it shall ye be brought forth.
O children of Adam, We have sent down to you a heavy garment for you, that you may conceal your nakedness and their adornment. That is better for the pious. These are the signs of Allah, so that they may reflect.
O children of Adam! Do not let Satan seduce you in the manner of Satan, as he did not let your parents seduce you, stripping them of their parents, so that their shame may expose them to their shame; and he will not see him from his tribe; they will see you. We have made the devils friends for those who believe.
And when they do commit an indecency, they say: "We found our fathers," and Allah commanded them: "Why do Allah not command those who do wrong?" Say: "Allah does not command the unjust."
Say: "My Lord has commanded justice, and you call your faces on each other, and worship Him with sincere devotion to Him, that you may worship Him, and He will bring you to a new creation."
He has guided the people, and some of them are astray; for they have taken the devils as protectors besides Allah. They have taken the devils as protectors. They think that they are guided.
O Children of Adam! Take the adornment of the Children of Adam, and eat and drink and drink, but do not waste, for He loves not the wasters.
Say: "Who has forbidden the adornment of Allah which He has brought forth for His servants, and of the good things?" Say: "They are in the life of this world." Say: "They are in the life of this world, and We do not believe in the Day of Judgment."
Say: "My Lord is only one of what is shameful, and what is hidden, and sin, and oppression that you associate with Allah, and that you associate no partners with Allah, and that you should say to Allah that which you do not know."
And every nation shall have a time appointed for them, but when their term comes, they will not have a single time, nor will they be able to delay.
O children of Adam! If there come to you apostles from among you, relating to you My communications, then whosoever fears Allah and his friends, there shall be no fear on them, nor shall they grieve.
And those who deny Our Ayat (proofs, evidences, verses, lessons, signs, revelations, etc.) and treat them with arrogance, they are the dwellers of the Fire; they will abide therein forever.
Who is more unjust than he who invents a lie against Allah or rejects His revelations? And when Our messengers will be given a portion of them, they will say to them, "Where are you whom you call on besides Allah?" They will say, "Where you call on Allah, they will be called to shame." They will say, "Yes, we will bear witness against us."
He will say: "Enter into the Fire the Fire before you and the people who were before you will be thrown into the faces of the people." When they will enter all together, they will say: "Our Lord! Our Lord! Our Lord has led us astray, so that they may be brought into the Fire." He will say: "Our Lord! Our Lord has led us astray."
And the first of them will say to the last of them: "You are not more than us, so taste the punishment for your deeds."
The gates of the heavens and those who deny Our signs, will not be opened to them in the heaven, nor will they enter Paradise until the eye of the needle will be opened, and they will not enter Paradise, for We shall requite the guilty.
For them shall be the Fire of Hell and coverings of them; and it will be the recompense of those who do wrong. Thus We recompense the wrongdoers.
And as for those who believe and do good works, We shall not impose any burden beyond his scope; they are the dwellers of Paradise; they will abide therein forever.
And We shall bring forth what is in their hearts, and rivers beneath them, and they will say, "Praise be to Allah, who has guided us for us. If Allah had not guided us, we would not have believed in him."
And the dwellers of Paradise will call out to the dwellers of the Fire: "Our Lord! We have promised us what our Lord promised us to do." They said, "Have you found the promise of your Lord?" They will say, "Yes!" They will say, "Yes, God is the curse of the wrongdoers."
Those who hinder from Allah's way and seek to make it crooked, and they will not believe in the Hereafter.
And there will be a barrier between them, and the dwellers of the mountains will know: "The people will know all their marks." They will call out to the companions of the Garden, "Peace be with you." They will not have entered it, and they will not be able to answer.
